el style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">1,000 screenings</=
a><span>. Now, just two years later, it&#8217;s done over 5,000 screenings.=
&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: =
26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>To date, Ezra has </span><strong>detected =
cancer in 13% of the people it&#8217;s screened</strong><span> and </span><=
strong>identified actionable clinical findings in a total of 70%</strong><s=
pan>.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Again, though, numbers are impersonal and c=
ancer is personal. One Ezra client discovered a brain tumor that turned out=
 to be glioma, a malignant but potentially slow-growing tumor that doctors =
told him could have taken 5-10 years to find otherwise. After a successful =
surgery, the client quit his job and started a PhD program at Columbia to w=
ork on cancer detection.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">There are many such stories. As=
